<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>The AI Discoverability Retainer — Executive Presence</title>
<link href="https://assets.calendly.com/assets/external/widget.css" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root{
    --navy:#1f3a5f; --blue:#2e6da4; --ink:#1a2230; --muted:#5b6577;
    --line:#e6e9ef; --wash:#f4f7fb; --good:#1f7a3d; --goodbg:#e3f1e6;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box;margin:0;padding:0}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  body{font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.55;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;background:#fff}
  .wrap{max-width:880px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px}
  .eyebrow{font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--blue);font-weight:800}
  h1{font-size:40px;line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-.02em;color:var(--navy);margin:14px 0 0}
  h2{font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.13em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--navy);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:18px}
  p{font-size:16px;color:#2a3340}
  .lede{font-size:19px;color:#33404e;margin-top:16px}
  section{padding:54px 0;border-top:1px solid var(--line)}
  section.wash{background:var(--wash);border-top:1px solid var(--line)}

  /* hero */
  .hero{padding:64px 0 58px;border-top:none;background:linear-gradient(180deg,#fbfcfe 0%,#fff 100%)}
  .pricetag{display:inline-flex;align-items:baseline;gap:8px;margin-top:26px;background:var(--navy);color:#fff;padding:12px 20px;border-radius:12px}
  .pricetag b{font-size:26px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.01em}
  .pricetag span{font-size:13px;color:#cfe0f2;font-weight:600}
  .epai-hook{margin-top:22px;font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);border-left:3px solid var(--blue);padding:6px 0 6px 14px}
  .epai-hook b{color:var(--navy)}

  /* metrics */
  .metrics{display:flex;gap:18px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:6px}
  .metric{flex:1;min-width:150px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:20px}
  .metric .n{font-size:30px;font-weight:800;color:var(--navy);line-height:1}
  .metric .l{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:6px}

  .twocol{display:flex;gap:26px;flex-wrap:wrap}
  .twocol .col{flex:1;min-width:240px}
  .card{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:20px}
  .card h3{font-size:15px;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:6px}
  .card p{font-size:14.5px;color:#3a4450}

  .quote{margin-top:22px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:0 12px 12px 0;padding:18px 22px;font-size:17px;color:var(--navy);font-style:italic}

  /* timeline */
  .steps{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px;margin-top:4px}
  .step{display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px}
  .step .num{flex:none;width:30px;height:30px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--blue);color:#fff;font-weight:800;font-size:14px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center}
  .step h3{font-size:16px;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:3px}
  .step p{font-size:14.5px;color:#3a4450}

  ul.clean{list-style:none;margin-top:6px}
  ul.clean li{position:relative;padding:7px 0 7px 26px;font-size:15px;color:#2a3340;border-bottom:1px dashed var(--line)}
  ul.clean li:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  ul.clean li:before{content:"";position:absolute;left:2px;top:14px;width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--blue)}

  .chips{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:10px;margin-top:8px}
  .chip{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:999px;padding:8px 15px;font-size:14px;color:var(--navy);font-weight:600}
  .fineprint{font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);margin-top:14px}

  .cta{background:var(--navy);color:#fff;border-radius:16px;padding:38px 34px;text-align:center;margin-top:8px}
  .cta h2{color:#cfe0f2}
  .cta p{color:#dce6f2;font-size:17px;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto}
  .btn{display:inline-block;margin-top:20px;background:#fff;color:var(--navy);font-weight:800;font-size:15px;text-decoration:none;padding:13px 26px;border-radius:10px}
  .cta .alt{display:block;margin-top:14px;font-size:14px;color:#aecbe8}
  .cta .alt a{color:#fff;text-decoration:underline}

  footer{padding:28px 0 46px;text-align:center;color:#9aa3b2;font-size:12.5px}
  @media(max-width:600px){h1{font-size:31px}.wrap{padding:0 20px}}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="eyebrow">Executive Presence · AI Discoverability</div>
    <h1>When someone asks AI who's the best in your field, are you the answer?</h1>
    <p class="lede">Buyers, boards, and journalists increasingly ask ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity for a recommendation <em>before</em> they ever run a search. We make sure the AI knows you — accurately — and recommends you.</p>
    <div class="pricetag"><b>$500 / month</b><span>month-to-month · per executive · cancel anytime</span></div>
    <div class="epai-hook">It starts with your <b>EPAI™</b> — a single score, like a credit score, for how discoverable you are across every major AI assistant. We measure it, then move it.</div>
  </div>
</header>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <p>We make executives <strong>discoverable, accurately described, and recommended by AI assistants</strong> — ChatGPT, Gemini, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and Claude. Traditional personal branding optimizes for humans scrolling a feed. We optimize for the models that are becoming the front door to your reputation: building the owned content, structured identity, and third-party citations that make an AI name <em>you</em> when it matters.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="wash">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Why it matters now</h2>
    <div class="twocol">
      <div class="col card">
        <h3>Search is becoming answers</h3>
        <p>AI assistants don't return ten blue links — they synthesize one answer and cite a handful of sources. There is no page two. Either you're in the answer, or you're invisible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col card">
        <h3>Two things define a reputation</h3>
        <p>AI discoverability (being found and recommended by machines) and human credibility (being respected by people). Most leaders invest only in the second. We own the first — and unlike the rest of reputation, it's measurable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="quote">"There are only so many authority slots in any niche. If you don't own yours, a competitor becomes the AI's answer instead of you." — executive presence as a defensive measure.</div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>Why we're credible</h2>
    <div class="metrics">
      <div class="metric"><div class="n">4 yrs</div><div class="l">building executive thought leadership</div></div>
      <div class="metric"><div class="n">400+</div><div class="l">executives served</div></div>
      <div class="metric"><div class="n">5</div><div class="l">AI engines scored every cycle — ChatGPT, Gemini, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, Claude</div></div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top:22px">Our clients are among the best in the world at what they do. The CEOs we work with have <strong>taken their companies public</strong>, delivered <strong>multi-billion-dollar exits</strong>, and run <strong>organizations of thousands</strong>. The best of the best trust Executive Presence with their personal brand. We've spent four years learning what actually moves a leader's visibility — and we've rebuilt that playbook for the AI era.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="wash">
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>The offering — $500 / month</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom:22px">A done-for-you AI-discoverability retainer. Month-to-month, priced per executive, run entirely in the background — no content calendar to approve, no posting required of you.</p>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step"><div class="num">1</div><div><h3>Start with your EPAI report</h3><p>We measure exactly how AI sees you today — whether each engine surfaces you, describes you accurately, cites you, and recommends you — and turn it into one score with a clear list of gaps.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="num">2</div><div><h3>We propose a plan from the data</h3><p>The report becomes a prioritized roadmap: claim your entity (Knowledge Panel, Wikidata), build your owned home, earn the citations that flip you from <em>described</em> to <em>recommended</em>.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="num">3</div><div><h3>Each month, we chip away at the highest-leverage item</h3><p>One focused move at a time, sequenced for the biggest gain per dollar — the way SEO retainers have worked for two decades, now applied to AI.</p></div></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="num">4</div><div><h3>A monthly report shows the impact</h3><p>Your EPAI, re-scored, with the trend line. You see real movement in how AI represents you — not impressions or follower counts.</p></div></div>
    </div>

    <div class="twocol" style="margin-top:26px">
      <div class="col">
        <h2 style="font-size:12px">What you get every month</h2>
        <ul class="clean">
          <li>A re-scored EPAI report card with your trend</li>
          <li>Execution on the highest-leverage foundation that month</li>
          <li>New, AI-optimized owned content published in your name</li>
          <li>Entity work (Knowledge Panel, Wikidata, schema) as needed</li>
          <li>A running tally of new third-party citations earned</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col">
        <h2 style="font-size:12px">Optional accelerants</h2>
        <p style="font-size:14px;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:8px">Flex up for a fundraise, a board search, or a launch — then flex back to baseline. Priced per scope.</p>
        <div class="chips">
          <span class="chip">Podcast guesting</span>
          <span class="chip">Bylines (Forbes / Inc / trade)</span>
          <span class="chip">Newsletter</span>
          <span class="chip">Social content</span>
          <span class="chip">Earned backlinks</span>
          <span class="chip">Wikipedia</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="fineprint">The $500 retainer is the always-on baseline that keeps your AI presence compounding. The accelerants — and the higher-touch human-credibility work — are how leaders dial it up when the moment calls for it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="wrap">
    <h2>"How do I know it's working?"</h2>
    <p>You watch your EPAI climb. Unlike impressions, followers, or "reach," it's a direct measurement of whether AI actually surfaces and recommends you — re-scored on a regular cadence, so progress is visible every cycle. A rising EPAI over three to six months is the proof, and the ROI story.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="wash" style="border-top:none">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="cta">
      <h2>See where you stand</h2>
      <p>We'll run your EPAI report, show you exactly how AI represents you today, and walk you through the plan to fix it. The report is the start of the conversation.</p>
      <a class="btn" href="https://calendly.com/justin-nassiri/ai-discoverability" onclick="if(window.Calendly){Calendly.initPopupWidget({url:'https://calendly.com/justin-nassiri/ai-discoverability'});return false;}">Book a call</a>
      <span class="alt">or email <a href="mailto:justin@executivepresence.io">justin@executivepresence.io</a></span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<footer>
  <div class="wrap">Executive Presence · AI Discoverability for leaders · EPAI™ is our measurement methodology · executivepresence.io</div>
</footer>

